LOCUS       SnoopCatcher             112 aa            linear   UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  SnoopCatcher: a ~112-aa protein partner split from the D4 domain of
            S. pneumoniae RrgA that forms a spontaneous covalent isopeptide bond
            with SnoopTag; this instance is the G848D variant (AMK38054.1)..
