FEATURES             Location/Qualifiers
     protein_domain  1..112
                     /label="SnoopCatcher"
                     /synonym="Snoop Catcher"
                     /note="Protein partner (~112 aa) split from the D4
                     (CnaA-like) domain of Streptococcus pneumoniae RrgA pilus
                     adhesin (residues 749-860). On mixing with the peptide
                     SnoopTag it reconstitutes the split domain and forms a
                     spontaneous, covalent intermolecular isopeptide bond (its
                     reactive Asn854 to the reactive Lys742 of SnoopTag),
                     irreversibly locking the two units together. Orthogonal to
                     the SpyTag/SpyCatcher pair. Canonical Veggiani 2016
                     engineered form (G842T + D848G stabilizing mutations),
                     deposit AMD39965.1."
